      <h1 style="font-size:2.25rem;margin-top:1rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem">Gas Pressure Washer Showdown: Simpson vs Professional vs VEVOR — Which Earns Its Keep?</h1>
      <div style="color:#64748b;font-size:0.9rem">June 17, 2026 · 18 min read</div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>The gas pressure washer market for contractors spans from $300 value options to $1,500 commercial-grade beasts. The specs all look similar on paper — 4000 PSI, 4.0 GPM, some kind of triplex pump — but the real-world performance difference between a $350 machine and a $1,200 machine is measured in hours of service life, cleaning speed, and maintenance costs over the first year of professional use.</p>
      <p>This comparison covers the eight most relevant gas pressure washers for contractors, organized by price tier and application. We tested spec sheets against real-world demands: concrete cleaning, fleet washing, deck restoration, and general job-site cleanup. Each machine is rated for the specific use cases that matter to professional contractors.</p>

      <h2>Comparison Overview</h2>
      <p>Before the detailed breakdown, here is how the machines stack up on the key specs that matter to contractors:</p>

